A stuck container train was looted at Sea Cow lake, Durban north, on Tuesday afternoon. Kevin Singh, director of security company Slovo Tactical Unit, said about 300 people descended on the train. Singh said: He said the train was carrying various goods. Singh said Public Order Police, Greenwood Park SAPS, the K9 Unit and other security companies worked to disperse the crowds. By 6pm, Singh said the crowd had been fully dispersed and the train moved. ALSO READ | Pinetown train station in KwaZulu-Natal remains closed due to looting cables theft.